class=m><span class=title>   Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> Thinking about doing a Hate Raid in the near future.  I was hoping that some of you might offer some advice on:<br>
<br>
1) How much will it cost me plat wise since I will provide everything.<br>
<br>
2) What do I need for a solid pull group<br>
<br>
3) General information on what to look for, and do?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance <p>Hala <br>
The seeker of his life <br>
Devoted Member of the Mighty Thunder Legion <br>
<br>
<br>
It is better to be hated for what you are then loved for what you are not.<br>
 -Andre Gide</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhaladormstoneblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haladorm Stoneblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 2/2/01 2:31:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 893<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/22/01 11:59:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/fenye.jpg width=92 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...</span><hr size=1> 1)Say you're taking 36 people.  5 people up per port, That's 7 stones to port everyone.  Take another 1 or 2 for safety, leave them on a corpse at the wizzie port.  30 Peridots will more than do you as long as you keep Marzin on only the puller, primary &amp; secondary assists, &amp; primary enchanters.  If you're killing Maestro, just default add Marzin &amp; Rune 5 to tanks, so that's another 2 Peri's per tank.  Ditto with Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
So let's say 36 people, killing Maestro only.  8 Stones at 210p each, &amp; say 70 peridots @ 10p each.  A little under 3k.<br>
<br>
2)Ideal pull group for me:<br>
-Experienced monk<br>
-56+ chanter (Can easily mes most mobs in the plane, doesn't have too much trouble with the harder stuff)<br>
-54+cleric (Has Remedy &amp; Marzin)<br>
-56+ shaman (Regrowth &amp; reliable slows)<br>
-55+ mage (CoH &amp; Malo)<br>
-55+ warrior (Primary assist to chain off the monk &amp; tough enough to take beats)<br>
<br>
Although it's not complete, I have a PoH guide up on Darkguard's guild page at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch">www.pangea.ca/~grinch</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> linked off the guides section. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 382<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/2/01 7:34:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...</span><hr size=1> Yep, Adune's numbers are right on.  I spent about 3k on prep stuff for Hate last night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganonstormwynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganon Stormwynd</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.angelfire.com/il/selectevil/icons/Icon_Fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/2/01 8:31:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.greyhawk.net/gano1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...</span><hr size=1> If you're careful with master looting, you'll also probably end up making money on the raid.  Cash drops in Hate are incredible.<br>
 <p>Ganon Stormwynd <BR>
Guild Leader<BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uorri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/3/01 1:21:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> I agree with all of this, except i might take twice as many peridots if the avg level of the raiders was 53 or lower. keep you pull monk buffed, naltron and rune on chanters.<br>
dont forget jasper. 40 per cleric should do.<br>
<br>
I'm a big fan of pasting myself with defense. /shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangharad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angharad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 502<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/4/01 11:02:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> sounds right to me as well<br>
but bring 10 stones to go to hate<br>
just in case <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
and lots of peris and jaspers is always good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubranndamerewyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branndamere Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/5/01 12:04:17 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://129.82.121.243/combinealliance/bios/branndamere.jpg height=150 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> I camp an alt at the port-up spot, to hold extra port gems, a coffin or two, and buffing regs. Less messy than leaving a corpse, but that's just me.  =)<br>
<br>
Don't forget to have some pearls on hand, to make your CoH mage happy, if you have one going on the raid. <p>Branndamere Wyndrunner,<BR>
55th Cleric of Erolissi Marr<BR>
Loremaster,<BR>
The Combine Alliance<BR>

"Every time you point a finger at someone else, remember - there are 3 fingers pointing back at you."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 397<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/5/01 4:36:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> 1)  Ok here is what I spent on components for 30 people:<br>
<br>
Port up stones (found in cleric guild in Neriak)  210 pp each x 7 stones (6 port groups + 1 extra) = 1470 pp<br>
<br>
120 Peridots @ 10.5 pp = 1260 pp<br>
<br>
120 Jaspers @ 0.787 pp = ~95 pp<br>
<br>
Total so far = 2825 pp<br>
<br>
Add in potential coffins and this goes up from there.  Shouldn't need too many coffins in Hate but its possible depending on where the wipe out occured.   I had my DE Enchanter bound at the WC Pyramid but camped in Neriak in case I needed to get coffins.  No clue how much coffins would run as it would depend on which summon corpse the necro had.  But I had access to 6k+ in cash so I would hope thats enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
While I won't comment on how much I got back in gems, coin, and cash items it did cover costs plus a nice extra.  Not as much as I could get soloing for 10 hours but enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Main reason to go is to help people get armor not to make money.  With the drops we got and the enjoyment I had I could have cared less if I didn't make anything back.<br>
<br>
<br>
2)  My pull group consided of:<br>
<br>
Monk (who likes to pull solo with a picker)<br>
Paladin for the picker (stun, dispell, and other spells makes for nice pulling, arrows work too)<br>
Enchanter  <br>
Cleric   <br>
Druid (snares, quick healing, buffs)<br>
Me (I've seen shaman here as well or a 2nd monk if the monks like to chain pull.  Adune and Masterrloo are amazing.)<br>
<br>
<br>
3)  Best thing I've found is just go, watch, listen, and learn.  Luckily I got to go with some of the best.  Thanks Kruunch &amp; Adune.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhaladormstoneblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haladorm Stoneblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/5/01 6:41:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just look'n for a Bit of advice...Hate Raid...</span><hr size=1> I'd like to thank you all for the input.<br>
<br>
Guess will see how it goes.  If ya see my name up in the Rants on Thursday night/Friday Morn I musta F'd up eh.<br>
<br>
As much as I would have liked to have gone up and watched learned, for all the raids I signed up for I have only gone on two. (not gonna rant on this, cause, well I dont have the time, I can easily see why not everyone gets to go on a riad)<br>
<br>
keep the posts and info coming.<br>
<br>
As much as I would have liked to of had the &quot;Perfect&quot; raid, with balance, experienced pull etc., doesnt look like that is going to happen.  Gonna be a learning experience for all.<br>
<br>
/ponders where all the casters are<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
Thanks again<br>
 <p>Hala <br>
The seeker of life <br>
Meat Shield of Thunder <br>
<br>
